description: This crash occurred on a two lane undivided roadway intersecting with another two lane undivided roadway with no grade and a posted speed limit of 48KMPH (30MPH). This crash occurred on a weekday evening.Vehicle #1, a 1993 Ford Taurus, was traveling on the two lane undivided roadway behind Vehicle #2, a 1996 Volkswagen Jetta, which was stopped at a red light. Vehicle #1 impacted with the rear of  Vehicle #2 with its front. Both vehicle came to rest in the intersection. Vehicle #2 was towed from the scene.The Ford Taurus (vehicle #1) was driven by a belted 19 year old male who was not injured. The driver stated Vehicle #2 had come to a stop and started to pull forward, but stopped again.

The crash occurred on a level two lane undivided roadway with a posted speed limit of 55 MPH (89 KPH).  The weather was clear, the roadway dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.     Vehicle 1, a 1996 Honda Civic, was traveling east on the roadway behind Vehicle 2, a 2002 GMC Envoy.  Vehicle 2 observes a non-contact vehicle in front of it slowing to make a left into a driveway.  Vehicle 2 decelerates and is struck in the rear by the front of Vehicle 1.  Vehicle 2 is pushed forward and drives off the road to the right coming to rest facing east off the south shoulder.  V1 came to rest facing east off the south shoulder.Vehicle 1 was towed due to damage and Vehicle 2 was driven from the scene.  Police did not consider either alcohol or illegal drugs to be involved and ordered no tests.

This two-vehicle crash occurred on a two-way, three-lane, not physically divided roadway.  The posted speed limit was 72kph (45mph).  There were no atmospheric conditions at the time of the incident and the roadway was dry.  Vehicle one (V1) was exiting a parking lot, which had a gradient of +2.  Vehicle two (V2) was going straight on a level roadway, passing the parking lot from where V1 was exiting.  There were no traffic control devices present at the location of this crash.    V1 a 1996 Jeep Grand Cherokee was attempting to make a left onto the westbound roadway from a parking lot from a convenience store.  V2 a 1992 Chevy Cavalier was traveling east on the main roadway at approximately 64kph (40mph).  The front left of V2 made contact with the left rear of V1.  The impact caused V1 to spin counter clockwise before coming to final rest in the westbound lane.  V2 continued further ahead before coming to rest in between lanes one and two of the roadway.   Vehicle two was removed from the scene due to moderate damage, whereas vehicle one suffered minor damage and was removed by the owner.
